The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 11 December is 1,549,660 (2,753.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 December, there were 88,104 new confirmed cases (156.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 November, there were 86,697 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (1,407 extra cases).
